laboratory_examinations.findings: Mild bibasilar atelectasis. A 7 x 9 x 5 cm phlegmon in the right upper quadrant of the abdomen involving the cecum and distal ileum. Extensive mesenteric fat stranding surrounding the phlegmon. Fluid tracking down the right paracolic gutter and collecting within the pelvis. No discrete fluid collection. The appendix is difficult to visualize; may represent a necrotic appendix. No pneumoperitoneum.
